# Test Maintenance

All Playwright specs live under `e2e/`, split by feature area (e.g. `accounts.spec.ts`, `navigation.spec.ts`). Shared helpers go in `e2e/fixtures.ts`.

When a UI component is modified in a way that changes what a user sees or interacts with (new button, changed text, new route, removed element), check whether an existing spec in `e2e/` covers that interaction.

- If an existing test covers it, update that test to match the new behavior.
- If no test covers it, add a test to the relevant `e2e/<feature>.spec.ts` file, or create a new spec file there if none fits.

## Selectors

Playwright tests use `data-testid` attributes for selecting elements. When adding a new interactive element, add a `data-testid` attribute to it.

## Deleting Tests

Never delete a passing test without explicit instruction.

## After Changes

After any test change, note what was updated and why.
